7 An Act relating to schools; providing an option for
public schools to report the departure of certain
8 students; requiring State Department of Education to
create a reporting portal; requiring portal to be
9 available online for public school administrators;
amending 70 O.S. 2021, Section 35e, which relates to
10 school dropout reports; clarifying language;
excluding certain students from the definition of
11 school dropout; providing for codification; providing
an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 24-162 of Title 70, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. When a student leaves a public school to attend a private or
19 other school, or to be educated by other means, the public school
20 administrator shall have the option to report the student's
21 departure has occurred.
22 B. The State Department of Education shall create a portal on
23 its website for public school administrators to report the
24 departures described in subsection A of this section.
