1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 35e, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 35e. A. It shall be the duty of the superintendent,
4 principal or head teacher of each public or private middle, junior
5 high and high school accredited by the State Department of Education
6 in the State of Oklahoma to notify the Department annually as
7 scheduled by the Department of the name, address, race and age of
8 any pupil dropping out from the school during the preceding year.
9 The report shall be made on forms prescribed and furnished by the
10 Department.
11 B. The State Board of Education shall cause these statistics of
12 school dropouts to be tabulated by grade and school district.
13 Information of school dropouts shall be made available to the
14 Oklahoma Department of Career and Technology Education, the Bureau
15 of Indian Affairs, the Military Department of the State of Oklahoma
16 for use in the youth educational programs provided by the Department
17 and the State Department of Health.
18 C. The State Department of Education shall make an annual
19 report to the Legislature prior to the convening of each regular
20 session thereof of information received and tabulated pursuant to
21 this section.
22 D. For the purposes of this section, "school dropout" means any
23 student who is under the age of nineteen (19) and has not graduated
24 from high school and is not attending any public or private school
